column1: Q3c:What should be UNRA's top three priorities on roads

column53: Old Masaka Road(Kyengera-Kabojja Secondary school turn off) (Kampala/Wakiso)

column2: Better Road Safety (Signs, Lines, Road humps)
Better road safety at night and security
Educate users about road usage/get their feed back
Construct inter-connection roads (feeder roads to main)
Construct more weighing bridge stations on roads
Consider and act on people's complaints
Award road contracts to efficient companies
put fly overs on roads and bridges
Proper inspection on road works and usage for better results
Improve quality of roads constructed especially murram roads
Increase the number of UNRA stations in the country
Construct reserves for parking eg boda bodas  and cars
Construct rural roads to standard tarmac roads
Compensate people who are owners of lands
Increase the length of climbing lines
Separate big vehicles lanes from small ones
Should put round abouts on most roads
Remove round abouts and sharp corners
Involving local people in road works
